  "body": "Those two services use the ETH sub-protocol, which is supported by most nodes in the network (unlike LES), so instead of using a `PeerPool` with hard-coded nodes[1] they should use one that employs `p2p.DiscoveryProtocol` to find and connect to as many peers as possible.\r\n\r\n[1] That is a dirty hack we needed because the discovery v4 protocol is terrible at finding LES nodes (#429)",
